    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen in visual/select mode, for a number of commands, I would like to cancel selection immediately execute the command in normal mode.\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n```lua\r\nvim.keymap.set(\"x\", \"a\", \"<ESC>a\", {})\r\n```\r\n\r\nLooking at prior issues it looks like NeoVim is translating some \"quick keys\" into escape sequences that does not occur in Vim. Is there a Lua alternative for switching modes to enable users to bypass <ESC> in general?\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nAdd the following remap: \r\n`vim.keymap.set(\"x\", \"a\", \"<ESC>a\", {})`\r\n\r\nMake any selection, say current line: \r\n`Shift + v'\r\n\r\nPress `a`\r\nNow wait, ... :^(\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nJust like we have vim.cmd and <cmd>, I would like to have a vim.send_keys with mode options\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.10.0-dev-5aa14e1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, 9.0 macOS version - arm64\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 14.2.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nWezterm, Kitty, and Terminal\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nnix profile install 'github:neovim/neovim?dir-contrib#neovim'",
